The paper deals with the problem of efficient quantization for information transmission over unreliable channels, which is a core topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed framework is applicable to a wide range of sources, including smooth sources (cs.MM) and Gaussian sources (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the connection between the proposed scheme and the Gram-Schmidt orthogonalization, which is a fundamental concept in linear algebra and signal processing (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed scheme in image and video compression (cs.CV).
